EIGHT zama zamas were arrested for illegal mining yesterday in Hlaneki, Mapuve and Mavalani outside Giyani, Limpopo have been denied bail. Seven women and one man briefly appeared before the Giyani Magistrate Court today (Friday) and were all reminded in custody until next week Thursday for formal bail application. The suspects aged between 31 and 65 are expected to appear in the Giyani Magistrate’s Court today for contravening Precious Metal Act 37 of 2005. Hawks spokesman in Limpopo, Captain Matimba Maluleke said the Hawks, the Public Order Police, Tactical Response Team, National Intervention Unit, Local Criminal Record Centre, Explosives Unit, Crime Intelligence,  Air Wing, K9, South African National Defence Force, Department of Home Affairs, Department of Mineral Resources, Department of Water and Sanitation conducted simultaneous disruptive operations focusing on illegal mining at the three villages.  Matimba told Daily Sun that "During that operation the integrated team confiscated a generator, hose pipes, saws, electric cables, hammers, 9mm live ammunition, gold nuggets,bags full of gold bearing material, pendukas, grinder and a app gas." "The confiscated goods are yet to be valued but they are expected to rum into millions. The suspects were found processing gold  when they were apprehended." He said